title: Light earthquake, 4.3 mag has occurred near Ambon in Indonesia
body: Light World Earthquakes Magnitude 4-4.9 A light earthquake magnitude 4.3 (ml/mb) has struck on Friday, 238 km S of Ambon, Indonesia (148 miles). Id of earthquake: us6000bhmt. Event ids that are associated: us6000bhmt. The 4.3-magnitude earthquake has occurred at 04:41:51 / 4:41 am (local time epicenter). A tsunami warning has not been issued (Does not indicate if a tsunami actually did or will exist). The earthquake was roughly at a depth of 399.09 km (248 miles). Exact location of earthquake, 127.8788° East, -5.8351° South, depth 399.09 km. Exact time and date of earthquake 14/08/20 / 2020-08-14 04:41:51 / August 14, 2020 @ 4:41 am UTC/GMT. Earthquakes 4.0 to 5.0 are often felt, but only causes minor damage. In the past 24 hours, there have been one, in the last 10 days two, in the past 30 days six and in the last 365 days twenty-six earthquakes of magnitude 3.0 or greater that have been detected nearby. There are an estimated 13,000 light quakes in the world each year. How did you react? Was there any damage to buildings? Leave a comment or report about shaking, activity and damage at your home, city and country. This data comes from the USGS Earthquake Notification Service.
